ball.dismissal: Akash Deep c Khaled Ahmed b Mehidy Hasan Miraz 12 (5b 0x4 2x6) SR: 240.00
ball.players: Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Akash Deep
ball.post_text: 4.34pm With that, India have declared! Sorry, Siraj. you won't get to smash some sixes here.
ball.text: don't pitch it up to him! Akash Deep has smoked that down the ground but on this occasion it doesn't have the distance and a tumbling long-on gets under it

ball.players: Mehidy Hasan Miraz to Akash Deep
ball.pre_text: Ankush Kulkarni: "@Vishal1686 In case India declared, is the light OK for the play to continue? " Right now, yes, but we have an hour left
ball.text: a big slog sweep from Akash Deep, he misses it but there's an appeal for caught behind and Shanto has reviewed it. It stayed a bit low after pitching outside off and there's nothing on UltraEdge

ball.pre_text: Rohit looks ready but India are not declaring yet. They lead by 51. Bumrah the new man
ball.text: gets some width first ball and he happily steers over the covers for one

ball.dismissal: KL Rahul st †Litton Das b Mehidy Hasan Miraz 68 (43b 7x4 2x6) SR: 158.13
ball.text: Beaten by bounce as he comes down the track and KL Rahul is stumped! Mehidy smartly bowled that short and outside off after seeing Rahul dancing down. The batter tried to whack it on off but the bounce beat his bat, Litton collected that around chest height off a spinner and did well to take the bails off

ball.players: Shakib Al Hasan to Akash Deep
ball.text: and one more! This is brute force. The fast bowler is using his strong shoulders and muscle to pack some power into these shots. He comes down the track and slaps it with disdain to the midwicket boundary for six more

ball.players: Shakib Al Hasan to Akash Deep
ball.text: whacked this time! Fetch that, Kanpuriyas! Pitched up this time and he absolutely slammed it high and long down the ground

ball.players: Shakib Al Hasan to Akash Deep
ball.pre_text: Akash Deep now. Will he take on Shakib?
ball.text: a big heave first ball against the line for the leg side boundary. Misses it completely

ball.dismissal: R Ashwin  b Shakib Al Hasan 1 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 25.00
ball.text: some dying "ooohhh"s from the crowd as Ashwin loses off stump! Tried to make room, Shakib darted one flat towards off stump and he missed the fiercely intended cut
sweeps the ball coming in this time to fine leg for one
Rahul makes room early and Shakib follows him, Rahul doesn't quite middle that shot punch
flat on off stump and it's chipped to midwicket after a bounce

ball.pre_text: Rohit is ready in his playing attire, tying his shoe laces. Declaration coming soon?
ball.text: what's happening here! Ashwin goes for the reverse and Mehidy pitches it way down the leg side, now off side and Ashwin is left a little surprised
96.2kmh, darts it just outside off, and Rahul pulls that with some power to deep midwicket. Mehidy is not going to give any flight here
off the mark with a deft and late touch fine on the off side for one towards deep third

ball.dismissal: RA Jadeja c Najmul Hossain Shanto b Mehidy Hasan Miraz 8 (13b 0x4 0x6) SR: 61.53
ball.text: that's a strange dismissal, the umpire's finger has silenced the crowd and Jadeja is walking off! He came down the track and Mehidy did well to drop it short and hit him on the pad. The ball then lobbed to Shanto at cover and he's been given out caught. That must have been bat-pad then

ball.pre_text:
Mehidy comes in for Hasan, around the wicket to Jadeja with a slip

"This was the type of innings India wanted from KL on the 19th of November last year...." Ouch! It's a team sport, Syed Kamran. India didn't lose only because of Rahul

Bj: "Hi Vishal. No way we will get 75 mins of play here. So I believe India will try to score as much as they can today and then declare overnight.Your thoughts?" Who knows India will declare today itself to bowl a little before stumps. Maybe for half hour?
ball.text: towards the leg side with the angle, Jadeja goes for a paddle kind of sweep and misses
91.8kmh, reverse sweep for a single. When was the last time Jadeja did that?!
stays back for the turning ball and pushes to mid-on
comes down the track and gets the inside half of the bat to leg for one
stays back this time and whips the ball turning in square on the other side
he comes out of the crease, Shakib pitches it wide and the batter manages to swat it away square on off for two

ball.pre_text: Hello hello! About 75 minutes to go for stumps with the extension. What's in store?
ball.text: turning in slightly and he helps it to leg

ball.post_text: Here's Vishal to see the day through
ball.text: In the slot... and it carries over! Did not look like he had timed it well. Rahul looked like he miscued the the loft off the length ball but it had enough to clear long-on
Length ball angling in on middle, punched through midwicket for two more
Length ball outside off, hangs back and guides it to deep third
Full on off, nails the drive straight back, long-on comes across to cut it off
Fetch that! Short and angling in, 140.kph, Rahul is up for it. Stands tall, swivels and pulls it through backward square leg

ball.post_text: Previous fastest team 250 was in 34 overs by England in their 2nd innings vs Pakistan in 2022 in Rawalpindi
ball.pre_text: Mahmud back on, around the wicket
ball.text: Jadeja makes room and steers the length ball to deep third to bring up the 250, again the fastest in men's Tests
Backs away to make room, gets a full ball that follows him, eased it down to long-on
Lands it around off, clipped to midwicket
